  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a user, I want to see opcodes in vmtraces so that I can debug my calls when they fail. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nRun `trace_call` on a contract call, and see the opcodes in the returned trace.\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nHello, \r\nWhen debugging failed contract calls that do not revert with a reason, we often want to turn to traces in order to debug them properly.\r\nIn besu, this means using one of the 3 trace types:\r\n- `trace` is useful for tracking failed contract calls\r\n- `stateDiff` is useful but only for stuff that actually changes the state, not so much for reverts/debugging.\r\n- `vmTrace` is great, except it only gives information using program counters\r\n\r\nThis means we need to use a disassembler, to turn the contract bytecode into opcodes, and then match the pc to that.\r\nIn practice, this means I have to use external tools every time I want to look at a trace.\r\n\r\nCould it be possible to have, in addition to the program counter, the actual opcode at that offset?\r\nThis would help _a lot_.\r\n\r\nThanks.",
